Instruments that use this filter transmission technique determine the absorption coefficient of the system by knowing the surface area of the collection filter (A), the flow rate of air passing over the filter (V), the sample time interval (Δt), and the light intensities at the beginning and end of Δt [46, 65–71]:bpf=AVlnIoIΔt\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
